2. I shall now consider this matter, with respect to the different Capacities and Abilities of Chrstians, for we may plainly see that God has distinguish'd some from others, by the larger Proportions of Gifts which he has bestow'd upon them, more then upon the rest; all Stars we know do not shine alike, for One Star differeth from another Star in Glory;
               1 Cor. 15.41. Some are of greater Magnitude and Splendor then others, but yet since all are Stars, all do and must shine; so now it is amongst Men, and amongst Christians, some are in higher Stations then others, of larger Capacities both for Natural parts and acquir'd abilities,

and have more and greater opportunities of doing Good then others; we will therefore distribute them into these 3 several Ranks and Sorts, and shew that all are oblig'd to do what they can in this matter, according to their several Abilities.
